parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to become stuck in a particular gear or unable to shift into gear, leading to loss of control, accidents, or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to shift into reverse or drive
the transmission shifts into neutral while driving
the vehicle stalls or shuts off
the gearshift lever sticks or becomes difficult to move
the dashboard display shows incorrect gear information.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch actuator can cause the vehicle to become stuck in a particular gear or unable to shift into gear, leading to loss of control, accidents, or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to shift into reverse or drive
the transmission shifts into neutral while driving
the vehicle stalls or shuts off
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Software issues can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to loss of control, accidents, or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to shift into reverse or drive
the transmission shifts into neutral while driving
the vehicle stalls or shuts off
the dashboard display shows incorrect gear information.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine compartment fires can cause significant damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to total loss, and pose a risk to the safety of the occupants and other road users.
symptoms: Smoke and flames emerging from the engine compartment
burning insulation mat
and fuel leaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Leaks and Fuel Pump Failures
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel leaks and fuel pump failures can cause engine compartment fires, leading to significant damage and safety risks.
symptoms: Fuel leaks
fuel pump failure
and fuel odor inside the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission and gear shift issues can cause unexpected loss of power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Gear shift getting stuck
difficulty shifting into reverse or drive
and unexpected loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine cooling system failures can cause engine overheating, leading to engine damage and potentially fires.
symptoms: Engine overheating
coolant leaks
and engine warning lights.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Recall Repair Delays and Parts Unavailability
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delays in recall repairs and unavailability of parts can lead to continued use of defective vehicles, increasing the risk of accidents and fires.
symptoms: Delayed or unavailable recall repairs
and parts unavailability.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine compartment fire can cause significant damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to a loss of control, accidents, or even fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly catches on fire while driving or parked
with smoke and flames coming from the engine compartment
often without warning signs or prior issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The shift lever will not go into park
the ignition key cannot be removed
the transmission slips out of gear
and the vehicle cannot be shifted into reverse or drive.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The air conditioning failure can cause reduced visibility due to fogging of windows, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The air conditioner fails to produce cold air
and the windows fog up suddenly
reducing visibility.
